   <head>¶ AD LECTOREM.</head>
   <l>DIcitur Augustus celebres fouisse poeta<gap reason="illegible" resp="#pdcc" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>,</l>
   <l>Et semper doctos excoluisse viro<gap reason="illegible" resp="#pdcc" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>.</l>
   <l>Hūc sibi magnificū Maro sensit, &amp; hūc quo<gap reason="illegible" resp="#pdcc" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap> Flaccu▪</l>
   <l>Sensit praesidium non mediocre suum</l>
   <l>Aetas illa quidem tanto sub principe felix,</l>
   <l>Sed tamen haec felix est{que} beata magis,</l>
   <l>Nam{que} sub Henrico clarissima principe virtu<gap reason="illegible" resp="#pdcc" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>,</l>
   <l>Ingenium, mores, eloquium{que} viget.</l>
   <l>Carminibus vates, Rhetor sermone diserto.</l>
   <l>Et studio floret diua Minerua sacro.</l>
   <l>Quo{que} foret tenere pubis spes ampla Britanni<gap reason="illegible" resp="#pdcc" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>
   </l>
   <l>Discere quae possit verba latina loqui,</l>
   <l>Aspice grammaticas normas, methodum{que} docendi</l>
   <q>
      <l>Praescriptum a Thoma praeside cardineo.</l>
      <l>O felix princeps tam clari fautor alumni,</l>
      <l>Haec coluit studiis qui tua regna suis.</l>
   </q>
   <closer>
      <signed>¶Thomas Cardinalis Eboae. &amp;c. Gypsui<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>chiane scholae praeceptoribus. S.D.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
